Ah, so the unicorn has been brought in. Your turn
is after the next one. In other words, you're just
the opening act.\n< Man >

When you go out, I'll grant you a glance. This
might be the last stroke of luck in your life,
after all.\n< Man >
...\n< Serena >

(Luck... This is supposed to be the last bit of
luck in my life?)\n< Serena >

(Fine by me, if this is what counts as luck. I
don't care if it's the last I'll ever have...!)\n< Serena >

(Oh, Splendour! The one I've been searching for so
desperately is now so close...!)\n< Serena >

(Finally... I've found it! I know where it is! All
that's left is to go on stage, receive the ring
from Cecilia-sama, and then return here!)\n< Serena >

(No more hesitation, no more fear. I feel courage
welling up from the depths of my heart.)\n< Serena >

(Just a little longer. Just a bit more patience. I
will definitely come to save you, Splendour...!
Once more, I shall hold you in my arms...!)\n< Serena >
...\n< Man >

Hm, ah. Yes, I've heard. The preparations are...
understood.\n< Man >
Hey kid, it's finally your turn.\n< Man >
Rejoice. Your auction is 'specially tailored.'\n< Man >

Do your best to liven things up, warm up the crowd
for us, will you?\n< Man >

...Hmph. Whatever it may be, I don't care. Do as
you please.\n< Serena >

endure it. Right now, there's nothing I'm afraid
of.\n< Serena >
?!\n< Serena >

fort...? Like, a route to the outside...\n< Cecilia >

brought me here...\n< Serena >

I figured... Ah, damn it...! Looks like I'll have
to lead the way...!\n< Cecilia >

So, I'm going to make a run for it, but it's
mostly guesswork! Don't complain if we hit a dead
end, okay?!\n< Cecilia >

Understood, I'll trust in you, Cecilia-sama, and
follow.\n< Serena >

...Please. Just stay calm for now... Alright,
let's go!\n< Serena >
